+# Solution for Issue #38286
+
+## Root Cause
+
+When a LINQ query uses `SelectMany` with an inline array where the array's values are **not** projected or compared against any typed column — e.g. `entities.SelectMany(e => new[] { "a", "b" }.Select(k => e))` — the query compiler creates a `ValuesExpression` whose row values carry `null` `TypeMapping`. This happens because:
+
+1. In `RelationalQueryableMethodTranslatingExpressionVisitor`, inline array elements are translated with `applyDefaultTypeMapping: false` so their type mapping can be inferred later from usage context.
+2. The `ColumnTypeMappingScanner` infers type mappings by finding typed references to the `ValuesExpression` column (e.g. comparison with a mapped column). When the array values are never used or compared, no inference is recorded.
+3. In `RelationalTypeMappingPostprocessor.ApplyTypeMappingsOnValuesExpression`, the inferred type mapping for the value column (`inferredTypeMappings[j]`) is `null`, so the constants keep their `null` `TypeMapping`.
+4. A `SqlUnaryExpression(Convert, value, value.Type, value.TypeMapping)` is then created with `null` `TypeMapping` for the first row.
+5. The SQL generator calls `sqlConstantExpression.TypeMapping!.GenerateSqlLiteral(...)` on the operand of that `Convert`, dereferencing a null mapping and throwing `NullReferenceException`.
+
+## Change
+
+**File:** `src/EFCore.Relational/Query/RelationalTypeMappingPostprocessor.cs`
+
+In `ApplyTypeMappingsOnValuesExpression`, the inner loop that applies type mappings to `ValuesExpression` row values was extended: when no type mapping was inferred for a non-`_ord` value column (column index `j > 0`) and the value still has a null `TypeMapping`, fall back to `ISqlExpressionFactory.ApplyDefaultTypeMapping` — which looks up the default type mapping for the value's CLR type from the type mapping source. This ensures every constant in every row gets a concrete type mapping before the SQL generator visits it.
+
+## Files Edited
+
+- `src/EFCore.Relational/Query/RelationalTypeMappingPostprocessor.cs`
+- `test/EFCore.Specification.Tests/Query/PrimitiveCollectionsQueryTestBase.cs` — added `Inline_collection_SelectMany_where_values_are_not_projected` regression test
